{% endblock %}
{% block content %}

  <h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">
  Having your say at the pre-application stage
</h1>
  <h2 class="pins-contents-list-title govuk-heading-s">Contents</h2>
  <ol class="govuk-list pins-contents-list">
    <li>
      <a class="govuk-link" href="#what-happens-next">What happens at the pre-application stage</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a class="govuk-link" href="#how-you-can-get-involved">How you can get involved</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a class="govuk-link" href="#what-the-developer-must-do">What the developer must do</a>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
      <div class="pins-step-by-step-section-main">
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="what-happens-next">What happens next</h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">Before the developer sends their application to the Planning Inspectorate, they must carry out a public consultation. This is the pre-application stage.</p>
        <p class="govuk-body">The developer must engage with:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>the general public</li>
          <li>parish councils</li>
          <li>statutory nature conservation bodies - these have a legal responsibility for birds, coastal areas or building heritage</li>
          <li>statutory consultees</li>
          <li>groups of campaigners</li>
          <li>local authorities and councils</li>
          <li>land owners and tenants</li>
          <li>other organisations</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="govuk-body">They must gather all comments and relevant information from members of the public and organisations. This allows you to have your say before the project application is sent to the Planning Inspectorate.</p>
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="what-the-developer-must-do">What the developer must do</h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">The developer must publish a notice in one local and national newspaper.</p>
        <p class="govuk-body">The advert must appear for at least two weeks and include:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>a description of the project</li>
          <li>where you can find details</li>
          <li>the deadline for sending them your comments</li>
        </ul>
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="how-you-can-get-involved">How you can get involved</h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">You can find the developer's details by searching for the project on this website.</p>
        <p class="govuk-body">You can also look for information in local news if you know the name of the project, or ask your local authority.</p>
        <div class="pins-step-by-step-navigation pins-step-by-step-navigation-next">
          <a class="govuk-link" href="/having-your-say-guide/registering-have-your-say">
